# Six of Cups — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P1_SixCups_R_Empathic
"Reversed, this card asks whether the memory you're holding onto has *changed* over time — not because you're wrong, but because that's what memories do. They're alive. They remix themselves."

You let that settle.

"Like a song you hear at eleven and then again at thirty — same track, different listener, different meaning."

Ellen exhales. Not relief — recognition. Like something she's been circling alone has just been said aloud for the first time.

"I've wondered about that. Whether I've been adding to it all these years. The strings — were they really strings? Or did I make them strings because it's more vivid that way? The voice — was it really that low, or has my memory been pitch-shifting it all this time?"

"Does it matter?"

"...I don't know. That's why I'm here."

