:: TheKind.Session1.P1_AceCups_U_Reframing
"There's a term in audio engineering — 'reference track.' The recording you compare everything else against. It sets the standard for the mix."

Ellen's listening. The professor in her recognizes a useful framework.

"This card says that night in the kitchen *became* your reference track for feeling. Not just for music — for all feeling. You measure every emotional experience against the purity of that first one."

She nods. The nod gets slower, heavier with recognition.

"Everything's so complicated now. Grief is complicated. Even listening to music is complicated. It used to just... hit me. I'd feel something and it was simple and total and I didn't have to *analyze* it."

She laughs a little. "I teach analysis for a living. God."

