:: TheKind.Session1.P1_AceCups_U_Empathic
"This card is about capacity. Before that night, you felt things the way kids feel things — big but formless. That record taught you that feelings could have *structure.* A beginning, a middle, a part that breaks you open, a part that puts you back together."

You meet her eyes.

"Your mom didn't just play you a song. She handed you the blueprint for how to feel."

Ellen's hands unclench in her lap. The knuckles go from white to pink.

"She was always doing that. Handing me things I didn't know I needed until years later." She pauses. "The first novel I ever loved — she left it on my pillow. Didn't say a word. Just left it there like it was the most natural thing in the world."

