# Ace of Cups — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P1_AceCups_R_Empathic
"Reversed, this card often means an emotion that got *stuck* — something you felt so deeply it never fully processed. You keep returning to this memory because there's a feeling in it that never got to finish."

Ellen is quiet for a long time. When she speaks, her voice is lower. More careful.

"She died in stages. Slowly. I was there for all of it. And I was so busy being strong — making calls, managing her meds, handling the paperwork — that I never just... sat down and felt it."

She looks at the overturned cup.

"And this record — this stupid record I can't find — it's the last time I remember just *feeling* something without managing it. Just standing in the kitchen, eleven years old, crying because my mom was crying, and that was enough. That was the whole thing."

The rain falls. The store holds its breath.

