# --- FOUR OF SWORDS ---

:: TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords
@if cards[1].reversed:
    The Four of Swords — reversed. A figure that should be at rest, but can't be. Restlessness. The search that won't let you sleep.

    Scout drums his fingers on the vinyl bin. Four of Swords reversed makes him anxious — it's the opposite of the listening state, the inability to sit with silence.

    Mal underlines something twice. That's rare.

    Delphi sets her mug down fully. Both hands on the counter.

    + ["Reversed, this card is telling me you *can't stop looking.* Not in a fun way — in an exhausting way. This search has become the thing you do instead of sitting with the grief. You keep the music playing so you never have to hear the quiet."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_R_Empathic
    + ["This reversal suggests the search itself has become a problem — it started as connection to your mom, but it's become a way to avoid *feeling* the loss. You're in motion so you don't have to be still. Like listening on shuffle so you never have to sit with the silence between tracks."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_R_Reframing
    + ["You've been looking too hard. Sometimes that makes it harder to find things."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_R_Practical
    + ["This card reversed means burnout. You're exhausting yourself with this search."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_R_Vague
@else:
    The Four of Swords. A figure lying still on a stone slab, three swords on the wall, one beneath them. Rest. Retreat. Sanctuary. Not death — *pause.*

    Scout exhales slowly. He recognizes this card's energy — the gap between tracks. The silence that's part of the album.

    Mal writes something with unusual care. Small letters, like a margin note in a beloved book.

    Delphi nods once. To herself, or to the card, or to the store.

    + ["This card says the record lives in your *rest.* In the quiet moments — falling asleep, staring out the window during office hours, sitting with Kuro on the couch. It comes to you when you stop looking. When you let the needle reach the run-out groove and just... listen to the room."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_U_Empathic
    + ["The Four of Swords is a sanctuary card. Whatever you lost, it's being *held* somewhere safe. It's not gone — it's resting. Waiting for you to be ready. Like a book you loaned to someone you trust — it exists, it's cared for, it'll come back when the time is right."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_U_Reframing
    + ["This card suggests you need to stop actively searching and allow the answer to come to you. Have you tried just... not looking for a while?"] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_U_Practical
    + ["Four of Swords means rest. Maybe you should take a break from the search."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_FourSwords_U_Vague
@endif

