# --- NINE OF PENTACLES ---

:: TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles
@if cards[1].reversed:
    The Nine of Pentacles — reversed. A garden that feels hollow. Self-sufficiency that's become isolation.

    Scout looks down. This card reversed makes him sad in a way he can't articulate — abundance without an audience.

    Mal's pen pauses. They look at Ellen, not the card. Unusual.

    Delphi's expression softens. She knows this card. She might live this card.

    + ["Reversed, this card says the life you've built is real and beautiful — but there's no one to share it with. Not no one, exactly. No one who *knew* you when the garden was just seeds. No one who heard your first draft and cried."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_R_Empathic
    + ["This reversal suggests you've built a good life but it feels incomplete. The search might be about filling a gap that's really about *sharing* — you want someone to listen with again. Not to music. To the world."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_R_Reframing
    + ["Nine of Pentacles reversed can mean overwork or feeling isolated despite success."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_R_Practical
    + ["This card reversed means your accomplishments feel hollow. Is your career fulfilling?"] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_R_Vague
@else:
    The Nine of Pentacles. A woman in a garden she cultivated herself. A falcon on her wrist. Abundance, self-sufficiency, the quiet pride of a life well-built.

    In the "Where It Lives Now" position, this card is saying something surprising.

    Scout cocks his head. Surprised by the card in this position. Good surprised — the kind of surprised that makes him reassess the whole mix.

    Mal writes two words. Underlines one.

    Delphi almost smiles. Almost.

    + ["This card is telling me something you might not expect. The thing you lost? It lives in the life you've *already built.* Your teaching, your routines, the home you've made. The record's warmth is already in your life — you just haven't recognized it wearing different clothes. It's in every playlist you make for a road trip, every song you hum while grading papers, every time you put music on for Kuro even though he's a dog and doesn't care."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_U_Poetic
    + ["This card represents someone who's cultivated a beautiful, self-sufficient life. Whatever you lost, it's been woven into who you've *become.* You carry it. You just can't see it because you're looking for it in a record sleeve instead of in the mirror."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_U_Empathic
    + ["The Nine of Pentacles is about abundance and independence. The lost thing might already be part of your daily life in ways you haven't noticed."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_U_Reframing
    + ["This is a positive card about material comfort. Things are going well for you."] -> TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_U_Vague
@endif

# Nine of Pentacles — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_U_Poetic
"This card is telling me something you might not expect. The thing you lost? It lives in the life you've *already built.* Your teaching, your routines, the home you've made."

You watch her listen.

"The record's warmth is already in your life — you just haven't recognized it wearing different clothes. It's in every playlist you make for a road trip, every song you hum while grading papers, every time you put music on for Kuro even though he's a dog and doesn't care."

Ellen blinks. Then her expression does something complicated — surprise, resistance, and then a slow, grudging recognition.

"He has preferences, actually," she says quietly. "He likes Ella Fitzgerald. He puts his head down when I play Ella."

"Your mom's influence."

Ellen looks at you. "How did you—" She stops. "Yeah. My mom loved Ella."

From behind the vinyl bins, Scout does a tiny fist pump. Only you see it.

