# Nine of Pentacles — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P2_NinePentacles_R_Empathic
"Reversed, this card says the life you've built is real and beautiful — but there's no one to share it with. Not no one, exactly. No one who *knew* you when the garden was just seeds."

Ellen's composure flickers. That landed somewhere deep.

"She was at my first reading. At Carruth." Ellen stops. Starts again. "I read this terrible story about a girl and a train station and she sat in the back row and cried. Not because it was good. Because I *wrote* something. She was the only one who ever cried at my writing."

The lamp light moves slowly across the cards.

"And she always brought music. Every visit. She'd drive up from Portland with a new record she'd found at Mississippi Records and say, 'Ellie, sit down, you need to hear this.' Even when I was twenty-five. Even when I was thirty."

