# --- EIGHT OF CUPS ---

:: TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups
@if cards[2].reversed:
    The Eight of Cups — reversed. Someone who tried to walk away but keeps coming back. The inability to leave the search behind.

    Scout goes still. This one he understands viscerally — the record you keep pulling off the shelf even when you know every scratch.

    Mal sets down the pen. Both hands flat on the composition notebook.

    Delphi wraps both hands around her mug but doesn't drink.

    + ["Reversed, this card says you've *tried* to stop looking. You know it might be futile. But you can't let go because letting go feels like letting go of *her.* And that's the real block — you've tied the search to your love, and now you can't stop one without betraying the other."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_R_Empathic
    + ["This reversal suggests you keep returning to the search even when you know it's not serving you. There's a pattern here worth examining — what does the *act* of searching give you that finding it wouldn't?"] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_R_Reframing
    + ["You keep coming back to this. There might be something about the search itself that you're not ready to let go of."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_R_Practical
    + ["Reversed Eight of Cups means you can't move forward. You're stuck."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_R_Vague
@else:
    The Eight of Cups. A figure walking away under a moonlit sky, leaving eight stacked cups behind. Leaving abundance to search for something unknown.

    Scout's grin fades. He knows this card — walking away from the collection, from the known catalog, to chase the unheard thing.

    Mal opens the composition notebook again. Resumes writing. Whatever they're building, this card adds something.

    Delphi sets her mug down. The sound is quiet and definite.

    + ["The Eight of Cups shows someone walking away from what they have to look for something they don't. And in the 'what blocks you' position..." You let that land. "Ellen, what have you walked away from to keep searching? What's not getting your attention?"] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_U_Empathic
    + ["This card says the obstacle is the search itself. You've been so focused on finding this one specific record that you've left behind other things that matter. The journey became a trap that feels like devotion — and that's the worst kind."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_U_Reframing
    + ["Eight of Cups often means abandonment — you might be unconsciously abandoning present opportunities while focused on this search."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_U_Analytical
    + ["This card means you need to move on from the search."] -> TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_U_Blunt
@endif

# Eight of Cups — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P3_EightCups_U_Empathic
"The Eight of Cups shows someone walking away from what they have to look for something they don't. And in the 'what blocks you' position..."

You let that land. Ellen's watching you carefully.

"Ellen, what have you walked away from to keep searching? What's not getting your attention?"

She goes quiet. Then, carefully:

"I turned down a sabbatical offer. I could've spent it writing. I spent it going through my mom's vinyl collection instead, cataloging everything, trying to match the four notes to something in her library."

The room feels different after this. Like a door opened and the air changed.

