# ============================================================================
# POSITION 4: WHAT FINDING LOOKS LIKE (KEY POSITION)
# ============================================================================

:: TheKind.Session1.Position4_Hub
~ session.discussed_cards.append(cards[3].name)
@render render_reading(reading=reading, highlight=3)

The last card. You touch it, and the lamp light shifts — the stained glass throwing a different color across the table. The store seems to lean in. The turntable behind the counter clicks — the arm lifting, resetting, as if the record player itself is paying attention.

"The last position. What finding looks like. Not 'will you find it' — what finding *means.*"

**Position 4: What Finding Looks Like**
**{cards[3].name}**{cards[3].reversed ?  (Reversed) | }

@if cards[3].name == "The Star":
    -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star
@elif cards[3].name == "Ten of Cups":
    -> TheKind.Session1.P4_TenCups
@else:
    -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World
@endif

# --- THE STAR ---

:: TheKind.Session1.P4_Star
@if cards[3].reversed:
    The Star — reversed. Hope that's hard to reach. Healing that's available but not yet accepted.

    Scout's hand is on a record sleeve. Holding it without looking at it. Like his body already picked the recommendation and his brain hasn't caught up.

    Mal is standing now. Somewhere near the boundary where the well-lit store starts to shade into the deeper shelves.

    Delphi hasn't moved. But the quality of her stillness has changed — she's not waiting anymore. She's ready.

    + ["The Star reversed doesn't mean no hope — it means the hope is there but you're struggling to *receive* it. You've been searching so hard, for so long, that you've forgotten how to just let something arrive. What if tonight, instead of looking for the record... you let The Kind look for *you?*"] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_R_Poetic
    + ["Reversed Star means you're blocking your own healing — not deliberately, but by keeping so busy with the search that you never sit still long enough to feel better. The cure is already here. You just keep browsing past it."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_R_Reframing
    + ["This reversal suggests healing is available but you're not accepting it yet. What do you think is holding you back?"] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_R_Practical
    + ["Reversed Star can mean loss of faith. Don't give up."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_R_Vague
@else:
    The Star. A figure kneeling by water, pouring from two vessels — one to the pool, one to the earth. The sky blazing with stars. After the Tower, after the darkness, The Star. Hope. Not the dramatic kind. The quiet kind. The kind that shows up after you've stopped expecting it.

    Ellen looks at it and something in her settles.

    Scout makes a sound — half breath, half laugh. The sound he makes when a song ends perfectly and he's not ready for the silence.

    Mal has moved to the edge of the deep shelves. Not going in. But oriented.

    Delphi picks up her mug. Takes a slow, deliberate sip. Satisfied. The reading has arrived where it was going.

    + ["The Star. After everything — the loss, the searching, the nights humming four notes into Shazam at 2am — this is the card that says *it was worth it.* Not because you'll find the record, but because the search brought you *here.* To this table, this moment, this conversation. Finding doesn't always look like what you expect. Sometimes it looks like a quiet night in a warm store with someone who's listening."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_U_Poetic
    + ["The Star is a healing card. Whatever you find tonight — a record, a memory, a new understanding — it's going to bring you peace. Real peace, not the kind you perform for other people. The kind where you can sit with Kuro on the couch and think about your mom and just... feel okay."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_U_Empathic
    + ["The Star appears after The Tower in the major arcana — the calm after destruction. Your mother's death was the Tower. This card says you're entering the healing phase. The search resolves from here."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_U_Reframing
    + ["The Star is a very positive card. Things are looking up for you."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_U_Vague
@endif

# Star — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session1.P4_Star_U_Poetic
"The Star."

You let the card breathe.

"After everything you've been through — the loss, the searching, the nights humming four notes into Shazam at 2am — this is the card that says *it was worth it.*"

Ellen watches you. Waiting.

"Not because you'll find the record. But because the search brought you *here.* To this table, this moment, this conversation."

You look at the reading nook. The colored lamplight. The worn hardwood. The rain on the roof. Scout behind the vinyl bins, listening. Delphi at the counter, listening. Mal at the edge of the deep shelves, listening. The whole store, listening.

"Finding doesn't always look like what you expect. Sometimes it looks like a quiet night in a warm store with someone who's listening."

Ellen's eyes are bright. She nods. And nods. And her hands unclench in her lap.

From behind the vinyl bins, Scout is definitely not crying. He is *aggressively not crying.*

The Kind feels warmer. The turntable hums a little softer. The rain sounds like music.

