# --- THE WORLD ---

:: TheKind.Session1.P4_World
@if cards[3].reversed:
    The World — reversed. Almost complete. One step from the finish line, unable to cross. The cycle wants to close but something holds it open.

    Scout is very still. His hand on a record, but not gripping. Resting.

    Mal has moved deeper. You can barely see them in the shadowed boundary of the deep shelves.

    Delphi is looking at you. Not at the card. At *you.* Like she knows what you're about to say before you say it.

    + ["The World reversed means you're *so close.* The cycle is almost complete — twenty years of searching, eight months of grief — and it all wants to resolve. It's pressing against you right now. Tonight. In this store. You just need to let it."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_R_Poetic
    + ["This reversal suggests you're delaying your own closure. Not deliberately — but some part of you isn't ready for the search to end, because ending the search means the story is finished."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_R_Reframing
    + ["The World reversed means completion is close but not quite here. There's one more step."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_R_Practical
    + ["Almost there. Reversed World means you're close to finding what you need."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_R_Vague
@else:
    The World. The dancer in the wreath. The four elements in the corners. Completion. The end of a journey. The last card of the major arcana — where the Fool's long road finally comes home.

    Ellen looks at it. Even without knowing tarot, she can feel the *finality* of this image.

    Scout lets out a long, slow breath. He knows. He knows this is the card that means the album is over.

    Mal has disappeared into the deep shelves. You can hear their footsteps — precise, unhurried, certain.

    Delphi closes her eyes. Just for a moment. When she opens them, they're warm and certain and the reading is done.

    + ["The World means a cycle completing. Your mother's life. Your grief. This search. They're all the same cycle, and this card says it's *ending* — not abruptly, not painfully, but the way an album ends. The last track fades, and then there's silence, and the silence isn't empty. It's *full.* It's full of everything the music was."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_U_Poetic
    + ["The World is the last major arcana card — the end of a journey. You've been carrying this search for twenty years. This card says tonight might be the night you set it down. Not because you gave up. Because you're *done.*"] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_U_Empathic
    + ["The World represents completion and achievement. This search is going to reach its conclusion — and it may be different from what you imagined, but it will feel *right.*"] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_U_Reframing
    + ["The World is the best card in the deck. This is a very good omen."] -> TheKind.Session1.P4_World_U_Vague
@endif

